    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix GUTI Type encoding function behavior\n\n### Summary\nThe `encode_u8_guti_type()` function in GutiType.c was not behaving as expected when called by external code. The function has been simplified to directly return the masked GUTI type value.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/GutiType.c`: Simplified the `encode_u8_guti_type()` function implementation\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/GutiType.h`: No changes needed to function signature\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `encode_u8_guti_type()` with a GutiType value, users were experiencing unexpected return values. The complex buffer manipulation code was functionally correct but confusing. \n\nFor example, when calling:\n```c\nGutiType guti_val = GUTI_MAPPED;\nuint8_t encoded = encode_u8_guti_type(&guti_val);\n```\n\nThe returned value should be 1 (GUTI_MAPPED & 0x7) but some users reported inconsistent behavior. The simplified implementation now directly returns `(*gutitype & 0x7)` making the behavior more predictable.\n\n"
}